divs: Sighting DetailsSighting Report: it was tuesday morning 6-14-05 at 3am ,the sky was clear and the stars were bright. i was takeing a break at work and as i always do i look at the stars. in the corner of my eye i noticed a large star like object moving slowly to the north .it was to large and to slow to be a satelight and it seemed to dull to be a star ,it just wasnt bright enough. i watched it move slowly across the sky,it was about the hight of a passenger plane .it slowly went over head and then it glowed a white light so bright that it seemed to light up the sky.as this happened i pickup speed and the white glow slowly started to get weaker till i couldnt see it anymore .thanks dean burgess
